# Model tiers — copy to .env and export before `studio run` / `make run`.
# Both tiers fall back to their committed pin when unset, so an empty .env
# changes nothing. Requires Studio with agent-YAML env interpolation
# (studio-foundation/studio#209).
#
#   SMART — the five whole-book verdict agents (section-filter,
#           alias-adjudication, entity-status/affiliation/species). One strict
#           JSON call per book over a large roster; a weak model drops the
#           contract (STU-624), so this defaults to claude-code.
#   BULK  — the high-volume map fan-outs (chapter-summaries,
#           discover/classify-relationships, wiki-pages). Where the token cost
#           lives; the cheap tier. Driven by config.yaml `defaults`.
#
# To run the whole pipeline on claude-code (both tiers), point BULK at it too:
#
#   STUDIO_BULK_PROVIDER=claude-code
#   STUDIO_BULK_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5

# STUDIO_SMART_PROVIDER=claude-code
# STUDIO_SMART_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5

# STUDIO_BULK_PROVIDER=ollama
# STUDIO_BULK_MODEL=mistral:7b-instruct

# LLM API keys — only needed for the cloud providers, and only if you declare
# their block in .studio/config.yaml (see config.example.yaml).
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_api_key_here
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here
